## Tech Stack

## Tech Stack

### Cloud & Data Platform
- Azure Storage Account (ADLS Gen2)  
  - Raw landing container for source data ingestion  
  - Hierarchical namespace enabled for analytics workloads

- Microsoft Fabric  
  - Lakehouse implementation using Medallion Architecture  
    - Bronze (raw ingestion)  
    - Silver (cleaned and transformed data)  
    - Gold (aggregated analytics-ready data)

### Data Engineering & Automation
- Microsoft Fabric Data Pipelines  
  - Orchestrates end-to-end Bronze → Silver → Gold processing  
  - Integrated notebook execution

- Event-Based Triggering  
  - Azure Blob Storage events (BlobCreated)  
  - Event Grid used to enable automated pipeline execution on data arrival

### Security & Identity
- Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)  
  - Authentication and access control

- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)  
  - Storage Blob Data Contributor / Owner  
  - Event Grid roles for trigger integration  
  - Secure access to Fabric workspace resources

### Analytics & Visualization
- Power BI  
  - Direct Lake semantic model  
  - DAX-based measures and KPIs  
  - Interactive dashboards for operational and performance insights

